**Key Information:**
- We have 8 independent observations from a continuous distribution
- π₀.₇ = 27.3 (the 70th percentile)
- Y₇ is the 7th order statistic (second largest value)
- By definition of the 70th percentile: P(X < 27.3) = 0.70

**Finding P(Y₇ < 27.3):**

The event {Y₇ < 27.3} means that the 7th order statistic is less than 27.3, which is equivalent to saying that at least 7 of the 8 observations are less than 27.3.

For each observation:
- P(X < 27.3) = 0.70
- P(X ≥ 27.3) = 0.30

The number of observations less than 27.3 follows a Binomial distribution with n = 8 and p = 0.70.

Y₇ < 27.3 means at least 7 observations are less than 27.3, so either:
- Exactly 7 observations are less than 27.3, OR
- Exactly 8 observations are less than 27.3

P(Y₇ < 27.3) = P(at least 7 out of 8 < 27.3)
= P(exactly 7 < 27.3) + P(exactly 8 < 27.3)
= C(8,7)(0.70)⁷(0.30)¹ + C(8,8)(0.70)⁸(0.30)⁰

