- The first 3 draws must all be white balls
- The 4th draw must be a white ball

Probability = P(1st is white) × P(2nd is white) × P(3rd is white) × P(4th is white)

Since we're sampling with replacement, each draw is independent:

Probability = (1/2) × (1/2) × (1/2) × (1/2) = (1/2)^4 = 1/16

Converting to decimal: 1/16 = 0.0625

